Default answer Yes to all questions.
nih -n -- answer no to all questions.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Update nih.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Keep MESSAGES in special file and tell user about it.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Variables NIH-{command} with options always applied, e.g.
 NIH_list=-q or NIH_list=-i. This will make special variables
 for install -l|-L and -p|-P obsolete.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

always "nih verify" before "nih uninstal/install"

nih deps should accept pkgbase or pkgname or pkgpaba but output what
is requested

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# nih update curl-7.33.0
Generating an update plan...
    R:1 U:1 A:0
Update plan cannot be built
================================
